article.description: Jonathan Williams scored 24 points -- his fifth-straight game of 20 or better -- including a 3-point jumper with 42 seconds left that put Tuesday night's game just out of reach as Toledo held on
article.headline: Williams scores 24 as Toledo breaks Loyola win streak 74-70
article.linkText: Williams scores 24 as Toledo breaks Loyola win streak 74-70
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Jonathan Williams scored 24 points -- his fifth-straight game of 20 or better -- including a 3-point jumper with 42 seconds left that put Tuesday night's game just out of reach as Toledo held on to defeat Loyola of Chicago 74-70. Jordan Lauf added 11 points with 13 rebounds for Toledo (6-6) for his first career double-double. Jaelan Sanford added 11 points and Steve Taylor. Jr. 10 points and 10 boards. Aundre Jackson led Loyola of Chicago (10-3) with 22 points, his 11th-straight game in double figures, but the Ramblers saw a five-game win streak come to an end. Jackson scored 14 points early in the second half as Loyola cut into an 11-point Toledo halftime lead. Milton Doyle, 11 points, cut the gap to 69-67 at 1:25 left. The Ramblers shot 52 percent in the half. Doyle has scored in double figures in all 13 games.
